args:
Chrom found himself unwittingly cast into a future
Grastaea mired in despair. After meeting Zethia
and resolving to fight alongside her, he came to
witness just how dire her situation had become...
*pant* We've barely made a dent in them!\nAnd yet if we don't stop them here...
Whew... I made it, but only just.
Thank you—and sorry for the trouble.\nI should be used to matchups such as\nthis by now...
No, this is far too many foes for one\nperson. Is there no one who will fight\nwith you?
No. Not after what I've done...
(The attacks are getting fiercer by the day.\nShe won't last much longer at this rate.)
(I have to help her, somehow. Perhaps...)
Yes. I led a group by that name in my own\nworld, dedicated to keeping the peace of\nYlisse.
I thought establishing a similar corps here\nmight lighten the burden you bear.

And though the volunteers were few,
and some laughed when I explained
my goal, I think we have the makings
of a spark.

If we use that spark to stave off some
of the gloom that's fallen over this place,
people will start believing in their own
potential once more.

I WILL see this through. And as the
Shepherds grow in numbers and
strength, I hope your life begins
to grow easier as well.
Of course, we would appreciate your\nstrength as well—but as a healer,\nnot a fighter. Can do you that?
If that is what you think best, I will happily\noblige. But I doubt the people of the\nHalidom will welcome my heali—ah!
We're under attack! I'll lead the charge. \nCan you support us from the rear?

This will be the Shepherds' first mission.
You have prepared well, but be cautious.
I don't want a single soldier lost this day!
Now, let's protect the Halidom!
Excellent work. Now, leave the rest to me!\nHRAAAH!
We... We won? We beat those fiends\nall on our own?
Yes, but the praise you've earned can wait.\nWe need to take the wounded back to\nthe Halidom.
Princess Zethia will tend to them there.
No one's gonna accept HER help.\nSure, we all know we're only alive\nnow 'cause of her, but...
We can't trust her after everything she's\ndone! If there was anywhere else we\ncould go, we'd have gone a long time ago!
I saw her, leading soldiers and fiends\nto put countless villages to the torch!\nI'll NEVER forget that!
Ch-Chrom, wait! Where are we going?
To the castle gate. We have many wounded\nthat need your attention.
They may claim not to want your help,\nbut I'd wager they value their lives more\nthan their grudges.
Eeeek! No, stop! I don't wanna die!
Do you still insist on this, Chrom?
Yes. I know you won't hurt them,\nand you'll prove that to them here.
*sigh* Very well. Please, sit still.\nThis will only take a moment.
You want me to sit still while you kill me?!\nI've seen what you do with that staff!
I can't believe it... I've never heard of\nanyone living after seeing the empress's\nstaff pointed their way.

Then I trust you'll make sure everyone
hears your account to the contrary.
Do the rest of you finally see the
princess as your ally?
Hurry now and bring the rest of the\nwounded. We don't have much time.
Captain! We brought the rest of\nthe wounded to be healed, as\nyou commanded.
Good. Then that brings our first mission to\na close. Well done.

The battle was tough, but things REALLY
got dicey after. Everyone was pretty jumpy
till they saw Zethia was actually healing
rather than hurting.
You're going to be fine. For now, just rest.
She's like an angel... Is this really the\nsame girl who supped on the screams\nof the innocent?
I've never witnessed this empress myself,\nbut the Zethia before you now seeks only\nto protect her people. She is a friend.
That she put a roof over your head should\nbe proof enough of that.
You doubt her without end, even after\nwitnessing her healing touch. How can\nyou still think she means you harm?
I... I don't know. I just can't get the image\nof what she used to be out of my mind.
It may always be there. But I hope that\nfrom here on, you trust her enough to\nlet her help you.

You've all endured incredible hardship to
stand here today. And to see the future
of hope you long for, you'll need to work
as one.
